      "title": "Spelled as spoken",
      "body": "Some everyday words look strange at first, because English spelling has been fibbing about them for centuries. was is 𐑢𐑪𐑟 — say it, that really is a z. said is 𐑕𐑧𐑛, rhyming with bed. And one starts with a w sound: 𐑢𐑳𐑯."
